laboratory_examinations.findings: Basal serum LH was 0.44 IU/L (normal ranges, 5–12 IU/L); During GnRH stimulation at 0 minutes LH was <0.5 IU/L, at 30 minutes it was 4.7 IU/L, at 60 minutes it was 4.5 IU/L, at 90 minutes it was 3.6 IU/L, and at 120 minutes it was 2.1 IU/L.

FSH was 0.50 IU/L (normal range, 2–6 IU/L); During GnRH stimulation at 0 minutes FSH was 2.1 IU/L, at 30 minutes it was 4.2 IU/L, at 60 minutes it was 5.8 IU/L, at 90 minutes it was 5.6 IU/L, and at 120 minutes it was 5.3 IU/L.
FAS levels remained low with mean plasma levels recorded at 0.35 IU/L (Chronic estrogen treatment decreased from 0.426 IU/L; P<0.01).
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: With estrogen treatment, FAS release decreased in frequency (1 vs. 3) and amplitude.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Inhibin B concentration remained below the normal values (<15 pg/mL).
